# .pgpass file for replicon failover operations
# Place this at ~/.pgpass on the old primary host so that pg_basebackup
# can authenticate to the new primary during rejoin without prompting.
#
# Format: hostname:port:database:username:password
# Permissions must be 0600: chmod 600 ~/.pgpass
#
# Example for rejoin (old primary connecting to new primary for pg_basebackup):
10.0.0.11:5432:*:replicator:your-secure-password

# If using a cluster with multiple standbys, add an entry for each potential
# new primary:
# 10.0.0.11:5432:*:replicator:your-secure-password
# 10.0.0.12:5432:*:replicator:your-secure-password
